  "issue_number": 220,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Pending-PR projection double-counts merge-ready PRs (`approvedPrCount` + `pendingMergedPrCount` are the same set), over-relieving the open-PR gate",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nIn `src/scoring/preview.ts`, `buildScenarioPreviews` computes the number of open PRs that will leave the queue as the **sum of three fields**, two of which the codebase defines as the *same set*:\n\n```ts\n// src/scoring/preview.ts:351\nconst userPendingCount = nonNegative(input.pendingMergedPrCount) + nonNegative(input.pendingClosedPrCount) + nonNegative(input.approvedPrCount);\n...\n// src/scoring/preview.ts:357\nconst expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge =\n  input.expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge !== undefined\n    ? nonNegative(input.expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge)\n    : Math.max(0, current.gates.openPrCount - userPendingCount);\n```\n\n`pendingMergedPrCount` and `approvedPrCount` are **the merge-ready set counted twice**. The authoritative producer proves it \u2014 `detectPendingPrScenario` sets both from the identical list:\n\n```ts\n// src/scoring/pending-pr-scenarios.ts:128-151\nconst mergeReady = classified.filter((entry) => entry.classification === \"merge_ready\");\n...\npendingMergedPrCount: mergeReady.length,   // :130/:149\napprovedPrCount: mergeReady.length,        // :151  \u2190 same value, same PRs\n```\n\nAnd the canonical \"how many PRs leave the open queue\" formula in that same file deliberately subtracts **merged + closed only**, never `approvedPrCount`:\n\n```ts\n// src/scoring/pending-pr-scenarios.ts:135  (the correct reference)\nconst expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge = Math.max(0, currentOpen - pendingMergedPrCount - pendingClosedPrCount);\n```\n\n`approvedPrCount` is fully redundant with `pendingMergedPrCount + pendingClosedPrCount`: `classifyOpenPullRequest` only labels a PR `merge_ready` when it has an approval and no blockers (`pending-pr-scenarios.ts:180-203`), and an approved-but-stale PR is classified `stale_likely_close` (\u2192 `pendingClosedPrCount`). So **every** approved PR is already in `pendingMergedPrCount` or `pendingClosedPrCount`. Adding `approvedPrCount` on top double-counts the merge-ready PRs.\n\n## Failure modes (concrete examples)\n\nThe bad `userPendingCount` flows into the open-PR projection (`:357`), `bestReasonableCase` (`:389` via `combinedPendingCount` at `:355`), the credibility projection (`:361`), and the scenario note (`:409-410`).\n\n### 1. Over-relieved open-PR gate (numeric score harm)\n\nA contributor has `openPrCount = 6` with 3 merge-ready PRs, supplied (as the GitHub-observed detector itself produces them, `pending-pr-scenarios.ts:149/151`) as `pendingMergedPrCount = 3`, `approvedPrCount = 3`, `pendingClosedPrCount = 0`, with no `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge`. `totalTokenScore = 90` \u2192 `openPrThreshold = 2 + floor(90/300) = 2` (`preview.ts` gate math).\n\n- **Correct (CR formula `pending-pr-scenarios.ts:135`):** `6 \u2212 3 \u2212 0 = 3` open after merge \u2192 `3 <= 2` is false \u2192 `openPrMultiplier = 0` \u2192 `afterPendingMerges` projected score stays **0** (gate not cleared).\n- **Current:** `userPendingCount = 3 + 0 + 3 = 6` \u2192 `6 \u2212 6 = 0` open \u2192 `0 <= 2` true \u2192 `openPrMultiplier = 1` \u2192 `afterPendingMerges` reports a **full positive score**.\n\nSo the \"after pending merges\" / \"best reasonable case\" scenarios tell the miner the open-PR gate clears when it does not. The same inflated `userPendingCount` feeds `combinedPendingCount` (`:355`) \u2192 `bestReasonableCase` open-PR floor (`:389`).\n\n### 2. Inflated scenario note (always reachable, GitHub-observed path)\n\nEven when `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge` *is* provided (the `github_observed` path via `applyPendingPrDetectionToScoreInput`, so the score itself is right), the note at `:409-410` still uses the double-counted `userPendingCount`:\n\n- 3 merge-ready PRs observed \u2192 the `afterPendingMerges` note reads **\"6 user-supplied pending approved/merged/closed PR(s) are treated as no longer open\"** \u2014 twice the real count of 3, and labeled \"user-supplied\" for a GitHub-observed scenario.\n\n## Reachability\n\n`pendingMergedPrCount`, `approvedPrCount`, and `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge` are independent optional inputs on the public surface \u2014 `src/api/routes.ts:310-313` and `src/mcp/server.ts:170-173` \u2014 and `detectPendingPrScenario`'s `user_supplied` branch passes them through unchanged (`pending-pr-scenarios.ts:97-107`, and `applyPendingPrDetectionToScoreInput` returns the input verbatim for `user_supplied`, `:210`). A caller that supplies the merge-ready count as both `pendingMergedPrCount` and `approvedPrCount` (exactly what the observed detector computes) without `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge` hits failure mode 1. No test pins this combination \u2014 `pending-pr-scenarios.test.ts:317` supplies `approvedPrCount` together with an explicit `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge` (dodging the fallback), and the other fixtures set only one of the two fields.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Call `buildScorePreview` (or the MCP/API score-preview tool) with `openPrCount: 6`, `pendingMergedPrCount: 3`, `approvedPrCount: 3`, `pendingClosedPrCount: 0`, `totalTokenScore: 90`, and **no** `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge`.\n2. Read `scenarioPreviews` \u2192 `afterPendingMerges`.\n3. Observe `openPrCount` projected as `0` (gate cleared, positive score) instead of the rules-correct `3` (gate still blocked, score `0`).\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe projected post-merge open-PR count subtracts each open PR at most once: `openPrCount \u2212 pendingMergedPrCount \u2212 pendingClosedPrCount`, exactly as `pending-pr-scenarios.ts:135` already does. `approvedPrCount` (a restatement of the merge-ready set) must not be added on top.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\n`userPendingCount` sums `pendingMergedPrCount + pendingClosedPrCount + approvedPrCount`, counting the merge-ready PRs twice. This under-projects post-merge open-PR pressure (clearing the open-PR gate that should stay closed), inflates the `afterPendingMerges`/`bestReasonableCase` projected scores, and reports a doubled PR count in the scenario note.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- In `src/scoring/preview.ts:351`, drop `approvedPrCount` from `userPendingCount` so it matches the canonical reduction at `pending-pr-scenarios.ts:135`:\n\n  ```ts\n  const userPendingCount = nonNegative(input.pendingMergedPrCount) + nonNegative(input.pendingClosedPrCount);\n  ```\n\n  `approvedPrCount` is already covered by `pendingMergedPrCount`/`pendingClosedPrCount`; if it is ever surfaced independently, do it as a separate display field, not as an additional term in the open-PR reduction.\n\n- Fix the `afterPendingMerges` note (`:409-410`) to report the de-duplicated count and not say \"user-supplied\" for `github_observed` scenarios.\n\n- Add fail-on-revert coverage: with `openPrCount = 6`, `pendingMergedPrCount = 3`, `approvedPrCount = 3`, no `expectedOpenPrCountAfterMerge`, the `afterPendingMerges` scenario must project `openPrCount = 3` (gate still blocked), not `0`; and a `github_observed` detection of 3 merge-ready PRs must yield a scenario note count of `3`, not `6`.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-02T04:52:32.000Z",
